name: Bright-rumped Attila - Attila spadiceus
description:
*Attila spadiceus*

Bright-rumped Attila

[MLZ:Bird:28427](https://arctos.database.museum/guid/MLZ:Bird:28427)

21 March 1941

Chacala

Nayarit, Mexico

Collected by Chester C. Lamb

Physical specimen held by the Moore Laboratory of Zoology, Occidental College, Los Angeles, CA

The polymorphic Bright-rumped Attila is a mid-sized flycatcher found from Mexico through to Brazil. Across its range, the Bright-rumped Attila has both rufous and gray morphs, different iris colors, and even different song types. This particular specimen is the subspecies found along the Pacific coast of Mexico "*Attila spadiceus pacificus.*"
